# CLAUDE.md вЂ” {{PROJECT_NAME}} Wiki LLM Schema

This file is the operating manual for any LLM working in this repo. Read it at the start of every session. It defines the architecture, conventions, page templates, and workflows that keep the wiki coherent across sessions.

> **Mirror with `AGENTS.md`.** Keep `CLAUDE.md` and `AGENTS.md` byte-identical so non-Claude agents (Codex, Gemini, Aider, Cursor) follow the same rules. Any edit to one applies to the other in the same change.

> **Self-contained repo.** Everything an LLM needs lives in this folder, including `.memory/`. The repo travels as a unit.

---

## The Hard Boundary: Wiki vs. Output

The most important rule. Internalize it before doing anything.

- **`{{WIKI_DIR}}/` is STRICTLY extraction** from the sources in `{{RAW_DIR}}/`. Each page describes what the sources say and how they relate. Cross-source "How different sources frame it" sections are extraction (a catalog of positions). Pages may note tensions/contradictions but may not adjudicate, editorialize, or argue a position the sources don't supply.
- **`{{OUTPUT_DIR}}/` is everything else the LLM produces** вЂ” syntheses, comparisons, blueprints, recommendations, decks, briefs, lint reports. Anything editorial/applied.

If you'd write a `> Editorial:` claim or a "what should we do / what does the corpus collectively argue" line, it belongs in `{{OUTPUT_DIR}}/`. The wiki must stay pure extraction so it can be cited as the substrate of any synthesis.

