Folder rule: person/entityв†’`{{ENTITY_DIR}}/`; named modelв†’`frameworks/`; ideaв†’`concepts/`; a documentв†’`sources/`. In doubt (editorial?) в†’ `{{OUTPUT_DIR}}/`.

## File naming
Lowercase, hyphenated, no special chars. Disambiguate slug collisions (a source titled the same as a concept в†’ suffix the source slug).

## Frontmatter (every page)
```yaml
---
title: "Human-readable title"
type: source | {{entity}} | concept | framework | synthesis
cssclasses: [<type>]
tags: []
created: {{DATE}}
updated: {{DATE}}
---
```
`cssclasses` must equal `type` so the page is color-coded. Source pages also carry `source-file:` (path into `{{RAW_DIR}}/`) for traceback.

## Wikilink discipline
`[[slug]]` for every entity reference вЂ” no bare names. Link first occurrence per H2. Ghost links to unwritten pages are encouraged (they surface gaps). Aim for bidirectional density.

## Raw-traceback protocol
Wiki is the working surface; raw files are the verbatim backstop. Read wiki pages first; open a raw file only for a longer/exact quote, to verify a paraphrase, or for exact page numbers. Quotes are short + page-cited: `> "quote" вЂ” *[[slug|Title]]*, p.N`. Full passages stay in `{{RAW_DIR}}/`.

## Operations
- **Ingest** вЂ” read source в†’ write source page в†’ create/update entity/concept/framework pages в†’ update `index.md` в†’ append `log.md` (`## [YYYY-MM-DD] ingest | Title`). Typical: 8вЂ“15 pages touched.
- **Query** вЂ” read `index.md`, follow `[[links]]`, cite pages; file substantive answers into `{{OUTPUT_DIR}}/`.
- **Lint** вЂ” scan for contradictions, orphans, ghost links, sparse/stale pages в†’ report in `{{OUTPUT_DIR}}/`.

## What NOT to do
- Never modify `{{RAW_DIR}}/`. Never read anything but `{{RAW_DIR}}/` into the wiki. Never put synthesis in the wiki. Never skip frontmatter. Never use bare names. Never fabricate quotes. Log every ingest. Keep `CLAUDE.md`/`AGENTS.md` identical.

